The paper is about formal verification and differential privacy, which are both topics in computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses probability measures and f-divergences, which are topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of liftings and composition principles suggests a focus on machine learning and statistics (cs.LG), while the use of universal quantification suggests a focus on theoretical computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper proposes a new construction for approximate lifting, which could be considered a topic in systems and control (cs.SI).
